# .trussignore — paths truss should NOT treat as workspace content.
#
# The project map (state/map.md) and `truss doctor` scan the workspace tree. Any
# path matched here is excluded from BOTH — it will not appear in the map and
# will not raise findings. This is the sanctioned way to keep foreign / bulk data
# inside the project without drowning the map and doctor in noise.
#
# Typical things to exclude: probe/raw data supplied for analysis, vendored
# datasets, ML checkpoints, build artifacts, VM images, copied app-support dirs.
#
# Syntax is gitignore-style: `#` comments, `!` to re-include, a trailing `/` for
# directories, a leading `/` to anchor to the root, and * ? ** globs.
# truss ALSO honours your .gitignore by default, so anything already ignored by
# git usually needs no entry here (set TRUSS_NO_GITIGNORE=1 to opt out of that).
#
# Agents: when you copy in bulk/foreign data that isn't part of the project's
# content, add its path here so the map and doctor stay focused on real work.
#
# Examples (uncomment / adapt):
# data/raw/
# datasets/
# *.tmp
# /vendor-dump/
